Atlanta’s premier free outdoor electronic music experience

Beats on the Beltline is a community-driven electronic music festival series held along Atlanta’s iconic BeltLine trail. Founded by the Connect collective, the event transforms public space into a shared cultural experience—merging music, art, and local entrepreneurship in one of the city’s most vibrant outdoor venues.

Each installment features 25–35 of Atlanta’s top DJs and emerging producers across multiple genres—from house and techno to drum & bass and bass music—supported by large-format LED visuals, immersive stage design, and full-scale production typically reserved for ticketed festivals. Drawing 5,000–10,000 attendees per event, Beats on the Beltline has become one of the largest recurring free music gatherings in the Southeast.

Beyond the music, the festival showcases 30+ local vendors, food and beverage partners, and creative businesses, fostering collaboration across Atlanta’s diverse creative ecosystem. Its mission is to keep dance culture accessible, authentic, and community-anchored—celebrating the freedom of public art, collective energy, and the unifying power of rhythm.

Core partners: Connect ATL, HORIZ3N, Park Tavern, Atlanta EDM, Simply Pop, and 404 Week
Attendance: 5,000–10,000 per event
Format: Free, all-ages, daytime outdoor festival
Location: Atlanta BeltLine, Park Tavern (Piedmont Park), Old 4th Ward Skate Park